📌 Project OverviewAntigravity is a "Split-Core" mobile application designed for Malaysian students studying away from home. It bridges the gap between Campus Survival (FinTech) and Remote Family Care (Healthcare).
The Problem
University students face high stress from strict daily budgets (RM15/day) and constant anxiety regarding the health of aging relatives in distant hometowns.
The Solution
A unified dashboard that uses Gemini Multimodal AI to manage food expenses and Vertex AI to monitor the vital signs of elderly family members remotely.
✨ Key Features
🏫 Campus Hub (FinTech)
Gemini Vision Buffet Scanner: Instantly estimates "Nasi Campur" prices to prevent cashier shock.
NFC Price Transparency: Tap-to-check real-time pricing for campus retailers using Firebase.
🏠 Care Hub (Healthcare)
Predictive Health Dashboard: Real-time monitoring of HR, SpO2, and Sleep via Google Cloud Healthcare API.
AI Fall Detection: Vertex AI Agent logic for instant emergency alerts.
Med-Liaison: Generative AI summaries that simplify complex medical reports into simple Malay/English/Mandarin.
🛠️ Technical Stack
Every component of Antigravity is built on the Google AI Ecosystem Stack:
Frontend: Flutter (Material Design 3 / Material You)
Intelligence: Gemini 1.5 Flash (Vision) & Gemini 1.5 Pro (Reasoning) 
Orchestration: Vertex AI Agent Builder & Firebase Genkit 
Infrastructure: Google Cloud Run (Serverless Deployment) 
Database: Firestore & Vertex AI Search (RAG) 
